  "texts": [
    "A rough interpretation of this metric is that it measures the probability above chance that two raters agree: a QWK of 1 indicates exact agreement, 0 indicates random agreement, and -1 indicates perfect disagreement.",
    "This metric is the standard in the industry established by Williamson et al. (2012) for comparing machine scoring performance.",
    "To evaluate automated scoring performance, we compare human-human QWK (the gold standard) to human-machine QWK.",
    "Note that, because ASAP does not include resolution scores (i.e.",
    "scores that resolve discrepancies between two human raters), we treat one human rater labels as the \"true\" score when computing human-machine QWK."
  ],
